28/02/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica said on Wednesday (February 27th) that Serbia can only enter the EU with Kosovo as part of its territory. Prior to any further talks on Serbia's EU membership, the EU should clearly define the Serbian territory it recognises, Kostunica told the television station Russia Today. He said there two main obstacles on Serbia's road to the EU -- the definition of Serbia and the deployment of an EU mission to Kosovo. 
Separately Wednesday, Kosovo Prime Minister Hashim Thaci announced that his government is preparing documents to join international organisations including the UN, the EU, NATO and the OSCE. At a government session, he also praised local authorities and international missions for making Kosovo safe. (RTS, AFP, RIA Novosti, Kosovalive, RTK, Telegrafi, Balkanweb, Tanjug - 27/02/08)
